!! Plugin discovery

The hub uses a single TW filter to find all rimir plugins:

```
[plugin-type[plugin]prefix[$:/plugins/rimir/]!title[$:/plugins/rimir/core-hook]sort[name]]
```

This excludes `core-hook` itself from the sidebar list.

!! State management

Selected plugin is stored in `$:/state/rimir/core-hook/selected`. If no selection exists, the filter auto-selects the first plugin alphabetically. The active sidebar item gets a `rr-settings-plugin-active` class via a `$let` + filter comparison.

!! Settings resolution

For the selected plugin `$:/plugins/rimir/<slug>`, the hub appends `/settings` and checks if that tiddler exists (across shadows + real tiddlers). If found, it transcludes the settings panel. If not, it falls back to `default-panel.tid`.

!! Naming convention

| !Pattern | !Purpose |
| `$:/plugins/rimir/<slug>/settings` | Settings panel (hub content + plugin detail tab) |
| `$:/plugins/rimir/<slug>/icon` | Plugin icon (sidebar + header) |

!! CSS classes

All styles use the `rr-settings-` prefix, defined in the theme plugin's `styles.tid`. The hub layout is a flex container with a fixed-width sidebar and flexible content area.

